## Capabilities-driven UI

- Fetch: `GET /capabilities` (persisted per `connectionId` after pair / device switch / Settings refresh).
- Onboarding: pair → **pull capabilities** (retry until success) → greeting.
- Nav tabs + More menu filtered via `ModuleNavGate.isRouteAvailable()`; hide unavailable routes.
- Do **not** add new feature screens unless asked — work with existing screens + Docker. Assistant chips = random 4 from persisted `assistant_tools`.

## Build / Firebase

- `app/google-services.json` (gitignored) — must match all application IDs (`com.template.app`, `.debug`, `.staging`, `.staging.debug`).
- Google Services plugin applied only when that file exists (`app/build.gradle.kts`).
- Flavors: `staging`, `production`; debug suffix `.debug`.

## Conventions

1. New feature: Screen → ViewModel → domain repo → `*RepositoryImpl` → API/DAO → `RepositoryModule`.
2. All Vela Room rows need `connectionId` from `ActiveConnectionProvider`.
3. Pairing via `PairDeviceUseCase` — never wipe device registry on add-device / onboarding.
4. Legacy filename typo: `Maintainance*` (intentional).
